<p>
	    <span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Now Available &ndash; CLIA Search located under the Healthcare tab</strong></span></span></p>
	<ul>
	    <li>
		<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>What is a CLIA Number?</strong></span></span>
		<ul>
		    <li>
			<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Clinical Laboratory Information Amendment Number (CLIA) was established to regulate all laboratories that test human specimens for the purpose of providing information for diagnosis, prevention, or treatment of any disease or impairment of, or the assessment of the health of human beings.&nbsp;</span></span></li>
		</ul>
	    </li>
	</ul>
	<ul>
	    <li>
		<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Who has a CLIA Number?</strong></span></span>
		<ul>
		    <li>
			<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">CLIA mandates that virtually all laboratories including physician office labs, meet applicable Federal requirements and have a CLIA certificate in order to operate.</span></span></li>
		</ul>
	    </li>
	</ul>
	<ul>
	    <li>
		<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Results returned from a CLIA search:</strong></span></span>
		<ul>
		    <li>
			<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Lab Information (name, address and phone)</span></span></li>
		    <li>
			<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">CLIA number</span></span></li>
		    <li>
			<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Lab Type</span></span></li>
		    <li>
			<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Certificate Type</span></span></li>
		</ul>
	    </li>
	</ul>
	<ul>
	    <li>
		<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">&nbsp;<strong>CLIA Certificate Level Details</strong></span></span>
		<ul>
		    <li>
			<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Certificate of Accreditation (COA)</span></span></li>
		    <li>
			<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Certificate of Compliance (COC)</span></span></li>
		    <li>
			<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Certificate for Provider Performed Microscopy (PPM)</span></span></li>
		    <li>
			<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Certificate of Waiver ( COW)</span></span></li>
		</ul>
	    </li>
	</ul>
	<p>
	    <span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">The price for the CLIA Search is $0.25 per hit.&nbsp; Price listed is exclusive of any applicable discounts or special price plans.&nbsp; Please contact your account representative with questions regarding the pricing in connection with your specific price plan.</span></span></p>
	<p>
	    <br />
	    <span style="font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Check out the new and improved Health Care reports.&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></span></span></p>
	<p>
	    <span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">In an ongoing effort to provide our health care clients with insight on providers who may pose fraud risk, we have made several improvements to the health care reports included in Accurint.&nbsp; These improvements include:</span></span></p>
	<ul>
	    <li>
		<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Additional data elements that are pertinent to the overall view of a provider</span></span></li>
	    <li>
		<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Updated presentation of information to make it more easily ingestible</span></span></li>
	    <li>
		<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Improvement to the report ordering options to streamline this process</span></span></li>
	</ul>
	<p>
	    <span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Provider License Report </strong></span></span></p>
	<p>
	    <span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">We have added a flag that indicates if the provider has opted out of participating in Medicare programs.</span></span></p>
	<p>
	    <span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">This is represented in the report as - Medicare Opt Out Flag &ndash; Yes/No<br />
	    <br />
	    We have also added to our address section a specification of practice and billing address.&nbsp; This information is pulled directly from the National Plan and Provider Enumeration System records.&nbsp; (NPPES)</span></span></p>
	<p>
	    <br />
	    <span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Provider Sanction Report </strong></span></span></p>
	<p>
	    <span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">The returned sanctions are now separated into two sections - Federal and State.&nbsp; This new categorization allows for better distinction between sanctions issued by a Federal Board such as the List of Excluded Individuals and Entities (LEIE) and the State Boards such as the Arizona State Board of Nursing.</span></span></p>
	<p>
	    <br />
	    <span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Comprehensive Health Care Provider Report </strong></span></span></p>
	<p>
	    <span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Now you can provide the following data parameters to direct report ordering by:</span></span></p>
	<ul>
	    <li>
		<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">NPI Number</span></span></li>
	    <li>
		<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Name and SSN</span></span></li>
	    <li>
		<span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Name and Full Address</span></span></li>
	</ul>
	<p>
	    <span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">We have also added additional data sources for deceased information on providers.&nbsp;&nbsp; This is presented as an option to include &ldquo;Additional Deceased Data Sources&rdquo;.&nbsp;&nbsp; It is important to note that this data will not return a Date of Death associated with the indicator of deceased.</span></span></p>
	<p>
	    <span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">We are also including additional sanction detail in the comprehensive report that will help determine severity of the sanction.&nbsp; Two new indicators are now displaying to indicate if the sanction was specific to fraud, waste and abuse and if the sanction resulted in a loss of license.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></p>
	<p>
	    <span style="font-size:12px;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">If you have any questions regarding these features, please contact your LexisNexis Account Representative or Customer Support at 866.277.8407 or <a href="https://accurint.custhelp.com" target="_blank"><b><u>Email Us</u></b></a>.</span></span></p>
